---
title: Korean-Style Beef with Broccoli, Ginger, and Jasmine Rice
description: Stir-frying is one of the simplest, fastest, and most delicious ways to get dinner on the table during busy weeknights. In this recipe, beef is marinated with intensely aromatic ingredients like soy sauce, sesame oil, hoisin sauce, and ginger for a restaurant-worthy result.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/korean-style-beef-ce33b318.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/korean-style-beef-996ca867.pdf
author: Michelle Doll Olson
cuisine: Korean
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/korean-style-beef-57f687ffbfba3d7be00f4592
servings: 2
course: main course
time required: 30 minutes
nutrition:
  calories: 548 kcal
  fat: 22 g
  saturated fat: 6 g
  carbohydrates: 52 g
  sugar: 6 g
  protein: 34 g
  fiber: 4 g
  sodium: 755 mg
---

Wash and dry all produce. Bring 2 cups salted water to a boil in a #medium pot{}. Mince @garlic{2%cloves}. Peel and mince @ginger{2%tbsp}. Thinly slice @scallions{4}, keeping greens and whites separate.

Add @jasmine rice{1%cup} to boiling water. Cover and reduce to a low simmer until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}. Remove from heat until meal is ready.

Flavor the beef: In a #large bowl{}, combine @soy sauce{2%oz}, @sesame oil{1%tbsp}, @hoisin sauce{1%jar}, scallion whites, half the garlic, and half the ginger. Add @ground beef{20%oz} and thoroughly combine with your hands.

Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{1/2%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium heat. Add @broccoli florets{16%oz} and toss until crisp-tender, ~{6-8%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Add remaining garlic and ginger, and toss until fragrant, about ~{30%seconds}. Remove from pan, and cover to keep warm.

Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{1/2%tsp} in same pan over medium-high heat. Add beef mixture and break up into pieces until browned, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Serve: Fluff rice with a #fork{}. Serve beef and broccoli on a bed of rice, and sprinkle with scallion greens and @sesame seeds{1%tbsp}. Enjoy!